    df.at[index, 'Violation Flag']=flag

In [75]:
compliant_after_df = pd.DataFrame(columns = ['Establishment ID', 'Inspections', 'Compliant After'])
In [76]:
temp1_reset = temp1
temp1_reset = temp1_reset.reset_index()
In [77]:
for index, row in temp1_reset.iterrows():
        
    last_valid_index = temp1.iloc[index].last_valid_index()
    
    compliant_after_df.at[index,'Establishment ID'] = temp1.index[index]
    compliant_after_df.at[index,'Inspections'] = temp1.iloc[index].last_valid_index()
        
    if temp1.iloc[index][last_valid_index] == 0.0:
        
        for i in reversed(range(last_valid_index)):
            if temp1.iloc[index][i+1] == 0.0:
                last_violation_index = i+1
            else:
                break
    else:
        
        last_violation_index = 'Not Compliant'
        
    compliant_after_df.at[index, 'Compliant After'] = last_violation_index

Here, it is observed that the number of restaurants that violates compliances tends to be higher around the month of August.

                )

class_map_data2 = go.Scattermapbox(
        lon = df[df['Violation Flag']==0]['Longitude'],
        lat = df[df['Violation Flag']==0]['Latitude'],
        text = df['Name'],
        name="In Compliance",
        hoverinfo='text',
        mode = 'markers',
        marker = dict(
                    color = 'green',
                    symbol = 'circle',
                    opacity = .6
                )
)

class_map_layout = go.Layout(
        title = 'Violation of Compliances in Restaurants',
        mapbox=go.layout.Mapbox(
            accesstoken=mapbox_access_token,
            center=dict(
            lat=39.1,
            lon=282.9426
        ),
            zoom=11
        )
    )

class_map = go.Figure(data=[class_map_data2, class_map_data1], layout=class_map_layout)
class_map.show()

In this graph, we see restaurants are mostly in clusters. Here, there are more restaurants which are not in compliance than restaurants which are in compliance.
